On the split half skull and / or the exploded skull,

Identify the bones that form the lateral wall of the nasal cavity, the superior (D) and middle (E) conchae are projections from the ethmoid bone. Realize that the inferior concha (F) is a separate bone that articulates with the maxillary bone (G). The lateral wall is also completed anteriorly by nasal cartilages.
identify the bones that form the nasal septum, the perpendicular plate of the ethmoid (A), and the vomer (B). Recall that the septum is completed, anteriorly, by the septal cartilage (C).
